AB  - SFG spectroscopy + ellipsometry; BSA at AWI. Microscopic surface chemistry (ion-protein interactions) directly controls macroscopic foam stability; BLG and BSA show different orientational preferences. Experimental evidence that AWI protein orientation affects foam stability — supports orientation component of commitment barrier. Note: BSA not BLG.
