TI  - Enhancing Foam Stability with β-Lactoglobulin Nanoparticles: Insights into Molecular-Level Interactions
JO  - Food Hydrocolloids
VL  - 148
SP  - 109290
PY  - 2024
DO  - 10.1016/j.foodhyd.2023.109290
AB  - Tensiometry, pendant drop, small-angle X-ray. BLG nanoparticles (partially denatured aggregates) form more stable foam than native BLG; hydrophobic surface patches exposed on nanoparticle surface drive enhanced adsorption. Hydrophobic surface exposure as rate-limiting variable for BLG adsorption — supports calyx SASA as the slow intrinsic variable. Note: SASA threshold language from older COMFHA framing is not applicable.
